@node "Introduction" "Introduction to G-Dec"
@next "Use"
@prev "WWare"
@{lindent 1}
@{fg text}@{bg back}@{fg text}@{bg back} G-Dec is a program designed to allow the decompilation of animted gif's to
a set of individual frame images, what this measn is that G-Dec will take an
animated gif file and export each frame to it's own file.
@endnode

@node "Use" "How to use G-Dec"
@next "Formats"
@prev "Introduction"
@{lindent 1}
@{PAR}@{LINE}
 G-Dec's interface is fairly self explainatory so i'll quickly run through
the basic operations of G-Dec.
@{PAR}@{LINE}
@{b}@{u}Selecting the Anim Gif@{ub}@{uu}
@{PAR}@{LINE}
 Click on the SET button next to the text box marked Gif file and @{LINE}
 you will be presented with a file requester allowing you to choose the gif@{LINE}
 file to decompile.
@{PAR}@{LINE}
@{b}@{u}Selecting the Destination directory@{ub}@{uu}
@{PAR}@{LINE}
 Click on the SET button next to the text box marked Dest Dir and@{LINE}
 you will be presented with a file requester allowing you to set @{LINE}
 the destination directory.
@{PAR}@{LINE}
@{b}@{u}Selecting the Export format@{ub}@{uu}
@{PAR}@{LINE}
 Click on the Set button (this is getting so repetative ;) next to the
format@{LINE}
 text box and you will be presented with a list of available export formats@{LINE}
 to select on simply click on ti and then press the select button.
@{PAR}@{LINE}
@{b}@{u}Decompiling the AnimGif@{ub}@{uu} 
@{PAR}@{LINE}
 Errrrrr click on the decompile button

@endnode

@node "Formats" "How to add export formats"
@next "ToDo"
@prev "Use"
G-Dec uses a customizable export system using binaries from the pbm
conversion system which allows G-dec to be configured to export frames in
any format you have a converter for.
@{PAR}@{LINE}
The format information for G-Dec is stored in the format directory located
in the same place as G-Dec itself, each file is a single line  ascii text
file  containing the name of the format the file name extension and the
command line  parameters for to convert the PBM temp file to the desiered
format, each is  seperated by a ; and also conatining %f for the temp file
and %o for the output file (case sensative).
@{PAR}@{LINE}
For example the format file for GIF's is 
@{PAR}@{LINE}
 GIF;.GIF;ppmtogif -interlace %f >%o; @{LINE}
  ^     ^    ^                ^   ^@{LINE}
  |     |    |                |   |@{LINE}
 Format |   Command line      | Out file @{LINE}
 name   |   Parameters        |  @{LINE}
       File                PBM Temp@{LINE}
     Extension               File
@{PAR}@{LINE}
And the format file for PNM is  
@{PAR}@{LINE}
 PNM;.PNM;COPY %f TO %o;
@{PAR}@{LINE}
So it is a simple matter to add an export format to G-Dec using the PBM
binaries, command line graphic's converter (Like GFXconv) or even scripts.
@{PAR}@{LINE}
               
@{PAR}@{LINE}

@endnode

